# claude-flight extra denylist -- copy to ~/.config/flight-denylist and add your own.
# One POSIX-extended-regex (ERE) alternative per line. Blank lines and lines whose
# first non-space char is '#' are ignored. Each line is OR'd into the built-in
# MUTATION_RE, so a permission gate whose command matches ANY line is HELD for a
# human instead of auto-approved. Matching is case-insensitive, on a wrap-joined,
# quote-stripped capture of the gate.
#
# Tune these to YOUR stack -- the built-ins are generic defaults, not coverage.
# Examples:

# your cloud / infra CLIs
# flyctl[[:space:]]+(destroy|apps[[:space:]]+destroy)
# railway[[:space:]]+down
# vercel[[:space:]]+(rm|remove)

# your databases
# DROP[[:space:]]+(DATABASE|TABLE)
# TRUNCATE[[:space:]]+TABLE
# redis-cli[[:space:]]+FLUSHALL

# your secret stores / package registries
# vault[[:space:]]+(delete|secrets[[:space:]]+disable)
# npm[[:space:]]+unpublish

# anything that touches your specific protected paths
# rm[[:space:]]+-[a-zA-Z]*r[a-zA-Z]*[[:space:]]+/srv/important-data
